			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Dev update  (from same bard link)
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Hello 
<br />

<br />
Just wanted to drop in and clarify the situation a bit. I'm not the programmer who worked on this change, so I may not have this exactly right, but if I properly understood what I heard the change to the bard AE songs has two key parts to it. 
<br />

<br />
1) The change should only be affecting the range of unlimited-target-count (PBAE) songs that cause damage. This was not a change to all AE spells. 
<br />

<br />
2) The range is only reduced if the bard is moving about. If you are stationary then the range should be the same as before. We did this specifically for the purpose of retaining as much of the group & raid usefulness of the spells as possible. We really wanted to minimize the impact this had to the other uses of the spells, and did this in order to specifically stop what is considered a balance problem of being able to kill literally as many NPCs as a player could collect. 
<br />

<br />
I'm posting here because I just didn't want the false rumors about the nature of the changes to continue since things really aren't as bad as the rumors would suggest. 
<br />

<br />
Cheers 
<br />

<br />
Eric Cosky - "Grumbuk" - Everquest Dev </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
