		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row2"><span class="name"><a name="55383"></a><b>Nadia</b></span><br /><span class="postdetails">Adventurer of Underfoot<br /><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~karl23/_images/nadia60.jpg" alt="" border="0" /><br /><br />Joined: 23 Dec 2002<br />Posts: 138<br /></span><br /></td>
		<td class="row2" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
			<tr>
				<td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=55383&amp;sid=868135455d0903740ec367a517e85f02#55383"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Mon Sep 06, 2004 2:08 PM<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
				<td valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=55383&amp;sid=868135455d0903740ec367a517e85f02"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">more dev feedback
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Hi folks
<br />

<br />
This post is to answer what questions I can and to make comments on various suggestions people have made. Hopefully I didn't miss anything.
<br />

<br />
One thing that is key to understand right now is that this topic is not closed, and that the final changes are still being discussed. Hopefully this will become an example of community involvement helping to find the best solution. 
<br />

<br />
There have been a lot of good suggestions. We're going to have a meeting very soon about this topic and try to come up with a better solution.
<br />

<br />
So here are my comments on various topics related to this, in no particular order:
<br />

<br />
----------
<br />
Re: Using Summoning as the "fix"
<br />

<br />
I don't think anyone likes summoning mobs. Summoning predates my arrival to the team but I personally always felt it was a crutch for bad AI. I think most people would prefer NPCs were smart enough to simply stop running in a circle after someone when it's clear they can't catch the player, and in general smart enough to deal with the exploitable situations that summoning is generally intended to prevent. Unfortunately for the time being major AI changes aren't going to happen but it's something we've been thinking about and hope to work on soon. Keeping the game strategically interesting is something I think is important to keeping it fun. But for the time being we can only tweak things, and summoning while not the optimial solution can at least solve some of these difficult problems.
<br />

<br />
-----------
<br />
Re: Removing part of the debuff, changing the behavior of part of a debuff.
<br />

<br />
The comments about the difficulty of disabling only part of a buff are based on this - a "buff" (or debuff) combines several component effects, and the way the system is set up, you can only remove the entire buff but not individual component effects. We might wind up making a new effect component that does something other than just a fixed damage over time; perhaps damage over time attenuated by distance, perhaps a new 'enable summoning of the caster of this buff' that I mentioned before, etc. It's still up for discussion, please continue with the suggestions.
<br />

<br />
-----------
<br />

<br />
Re: Why we are doing it at all
<br />

<br />
It's not just server load, it's not just the unbalanced high DPS, it's not just the exp rate resulting from that DPS, it's not just the effect it has to other players in the zone, it's not just the macroers getting risk free powerlevelling - it's all of these that combined become something relevant enough that we want to fix it. It's not related to the fact that it's soloing, or some other classes envy, or anything else along those lines. 
<br />

<br />
------------
<br />

<br />
Re: Compensation for fixing a broken part of the game
<br />

<br />
The idea that anyone should be getting something "to compensate" for us fixing the game isn't something that makes sense to me. Yes, after we are done you won't be able to AE kite 30, 40, 100+ NPCs at once. Should players be given some new ability because they can no longer do this? I wouldn't advise that be done, because I see this as a fix not some kind of trade, but that's up to the design team. I just write code and try to occasionally facilitate discussion with the players when it seems appropriate (like this).
<br />

<br />
------------
<br />
Re: Just remove the damage part of the songs
<br />

<br />
We are hoping to find a solution that changes the gameplay of bards less than that. These songs can be pretty darn useful, and it is very much a goal to minimize the effect to the entire population with these changes. We're all hoping to find a solution that leaves the songs substantially the same, but only prevents what we consider to be the problem. Removing the damage part of the songs would prevent their use for farming and the other stuff that really isn't part of the problem, and we'd like to minimize the impact.
<br />

<br />
------------
<br />
Re: Why not just add new spells to NPCs, or archery items, thrown rocks, whatever
<br />

<br />
The problem with this is this would require designers to go through every zone and modify all the NPCs. QA would have to review everything. In short, this is way too much work. We have no problem with work, we do it all day, but I think everyone would prefer we chose a solution that required the minimum amount of time on this so we could correct other problems with the time saved. In other words, if two ways to solve a problem are available, it's smart to do the one that takes less time so long as the solution is effective. It's pretty widely agreed here that if we make careful changes to the mechanic we can achieve the goal that would be just as good or better than any global changes to the NPCs that would be so much more time consuming to do.
<br />

<br />
------------
<br />
Re: Bards having to stand still
<br />

<br />
I fully appreciate not wanting to stand still at any time as a bard. As some of you know, I have played a lot of EQ and one character was a bard that I played to 65 with 120AA or so which I know isn't much by today's standards but trust me when I say I don't want to see bards ever having to stand still to cast. I'm going to make sure everyone around here understands how important this is to people who play bards. For those wondering, the bard is only one of the many classes I played a lot of and I like to think I have a reasonably unbiased and educated view of the classes in general . I think this may be one of the reasons why they let me join the team  (and no I haven't buffed my characters with my GM account -it's the real deal).
<br />

<br />
------------
<br />
Re: Adding variable run speed to NPCs
<br />

<br />
I think perhaps the biggest concern here is that it's changing a fundamental behavior of NPCs and that it could affect all kinds of other stuff such as pulling for normal groups, etc. We're trying to keep any changes more specific to the problem and this kind of thing could have a pretty broad impact.
<br />

<br />
-------------
<br />
Re: Macroers & PBAE kiting
<br />

<br />
This is one of the (many) reasons we want it fixed; right now macroers can just warp around and get risk free exp. I've personally verified that this is true. We're trying to solve the bigger macro problem one thing at a time, and whatever we implement here we want to be sure it makes macroing as ineffective as possible. 
<br />

<br />
-------------
<br />
Re: Extended range & focus effects
<br />

<br />
Extended range was never described as a range extension to anything other than beneficial songs. Just because it was affecting all songs for a while doesn't mean that this other unrelated issue should cause that AA to be redefined. 
<br />

<br />
That said I never really understood why focus effects don't work for bards, but that's a question for the design team. 
<br />

<br />
--------------
<br />
Re: Committment to the game and false claims that we are in a "Maintenance Mode"
<br />

<br />
We have a staff of well over 50 people working full time on new EverQuest Live content and bug fixes for old content. This is a far cry from a maintenance mode project. Personally I hope to see EQ last a long, long time because it's a lot of fun to work on a game I play so much of. After working on so many projects from the ground up in the past where you are always reinventing the wheel just to get things rolling, working on a project that is basically a stable platform for the development of new ideas is really fun. 
<br />

<br />
--------------
<br />
Re: Taking the time to fix it "Right"
<br />

<br />
We do plan to fix it "right". That's the goal. We want the best solution to the problem that has the least negative impact to anyone's fun. To suggest we are lazy or not interested in making the effort to do this "right" is pretty far from the truth. We take pride in our work and want everything we do to be done well. Note that this still means if we think two solutions have about the same pros & cons we'll probably want to do the one that takes less time. It's reasonable for anyone who values their time to do that.
<br />

<br />
--------------
<br />
Re: EQ2 somehow influencing these decisions
<br />

<br />
I can say without hesitation that this has nothing to do with EQ2. We make decisions like these for the health of EverQuest, that's all there is to it.
<br />

<br />
---------------
<br />
Re: This was some kind of rushed fix.
<br />

<br />
This was hardly a rushed fix. It was something that had been percolating for a while, and finally it seemed like a good idea to work on it, so we made the change and put it on the Test server. Clearly it's not the best solution so we'll be looking into it more.
<br />

<br />
----------------
<br />
Re: Why not just have GMs monitor for bad behavior and start banning people?
<br />

<br />
Makes a lot more sense to just correct the game so GMs can spend their time doing more useful stuff.
<br />

<br />
----------------
<br />
Re: Possibly use mana as the solution to PBAE kiting.
<br />

<br />
It's an idea, not a bad one. We'll talk about it during our meeting. It's definitely a simple change. I don't personally care for this approach because it would hurt more casual players who don't have all the mana regen items they want.
<br />

<br />
----------------
<br />
Re: Scaling up 54 song
<br />

<br />
I'd guess this isn't a good way to go since the 54 song has other properties that prevent it from being used as much. As several had suggested, a scaled up version of the level 20 would make more sense. Probably makes even more sense though to adjust the existing spells though so they can continue to be used mostly the same way as they are now with changes specifically designed to prevent PBAE kiting. The goal is after all to minimize the impact to the other uses for these songs.
<br />

<br />
----------------
<br />
Re: Increasing melee range of NPCs
<br />

<br />
This is another case of affecting the entire game instead of having a specifically targeted fix. We'd prefer to do something that affects the game as little as possible.
<br />

<br />
----------------
<br />

<br />
Re: Sony "hates soloing"
<br />

<br />
This is just my opinion, but personally I like soloing. I know a number of folks here like to also. I hope to see all classes be able to solo at a productive level, at something less than but not horribly less than group based experience rates because I think that grouping and social interaction is a key part of keeping the game fun. But I'm also very aware of the constraints real life can put on a person, and sometimes soloing is the only way to have fun for a bit and I think it's reasonable to expect to be able to do it with any class. Again, this is just my opinion. Making all the classes able to solo without unbalancing existing group content would be a huge and complicated task but who knows, maybe it will happen someday. There's probably a way to make it work.
<br />

<br />

<br />
----------------
<br />

<br />

<br />
I hope this helps folks understand what's going on at our end. 
<br />

<br />
Cheers 
<br />

<br />
Eric Cosky - "Grumbuk"
<br />
Assistant Lead Programmer, EverQuest
<br />
Sony Online Entertainment 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
